Hilal Browser: enable transparent macOS chrome surfaces

Makes Hilal top-level macOS windows stay non-opaque, enables native
macOS vibrancy behind the browser chrome, and removes the opaque Firefox
backstops that otherwise keep the toolbar, sidebar, and content frame white.
The chrome styling is applied unconditionally on macOS for Hilal builds so
the vertical tabs sidebar, toolbar, and tab panels sit on readable frosted
Tahoe-style surfaces instead of either opaque Firefox white or fully clear glass.

---
diff --git a/browser/extensions/newtab/content-src/styles/activity-stream.scss b/browser/extensions/newtab/content-src/styles/activity-stream.scss
index 4ac1348a809a..a1f67b64499b 100644
--- a/browser/extensions/newtab/content-src/styles/activity-stream.scss
+++ b/browser/extensions/newtab/content-src/styles/activity-stream.scss
@@ -42,6 +42,23 @@ body {
   overflow-y: scroll;
 }
 
+@media (-moz-platform: macos) {
+  :root {
+    --newtab-background-color: transparent;
+    --newtab-background-color-secondary: light-dark(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.78), rgba(42, 41, 49, 0.68));
+    --newtab-background-card: light-dark(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.68), rgba(66, 65, 77, 0.58));
+    --newtab-weather-background-color: light-dark(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.66), rgba(66, 65, 77, 0.56));
+    --newtab-overlay-color: light-dark(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.58), rgba(43, 42, 51, 0.5));
+  }
+
+  html,
+  body,
+  #root,
+  .activity-stream {
+    background-color: transparent;
+  }
+}
+
 h1,
 h2 {
   font-weight: var(--font-weight);
